This paper deals with the management of distributed file systems in cluster computing, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning for predicting file access patterns, which is related to topics in Databases (cs.DB) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of storage tiering, which is related to topics in Operating Systems (cs.OS). Finally, the paper uses machine learning for dynamic refinement of models, which is related to topics in Machine Learning (cs.LG).
